Subject: User PCDAAIDMR01 cannot see Stealthbits features via web browsers
Description:
One of GE Team from ID Management team unable to manage users account due to don't have permission to StealthAudit web console.

Previously we have onboarded ID PCDAAIDMR01 to the AD servers for user AD group. Now this user can login to the web console.
DevOps_Steps_to_Reproduce__c:
1. Create a new AD user account and not assign any web related role to the user.
2. Login to Web reporting module.
What_We_Know__c: The customer added incorrect user account to NEA User Access settings. Issue was resolved in today's meeting
Solution_Comment__c:
Symptom
When the user PCDAAIDMR01 tried to login to StealthAUDIT Reporting web module, the user could not view any reports.

Cause
The user was not added to correct role in StealthAUDIT.

Resolution
To resolve this issue, we added the user to correct role inside User Access settings and issue was resolved.
We also discussed that Reporting module does not provide any administrator functionality like adding or removing a user. tThis has to be done from the StealthAUDIT desktop application. We also verified the user access settings in StealthDEFEND and resolved the issue with action service.
